# Card Store

A full-stack trading card collection manager built with Python (Flask) and vanilla HTML/CSS/JavaScript.

---

## Resources

### User
| Attribute      | Type   | Description                          |
|----------------|--------|--------------------------------------|
| id             | int    | Primary key (auto-increment)         |
| first_name     | text   | User's first name                    |
| last_name      | text   | User's last name                     |
| email          | text   | Unique email address (lowercase)     |
| password_hash  | text   | PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA256 hash + salt       |

### Card
| Attribute  | Type  | Description                      |
|------------|-------|----------------------------------|
| id         | int   | Primary key (auto-increment)     |
| name       | text  | Card name                        |
| set_name   | text  | Set the card belongs to          |
| condition  | text  | Card condition (e.g. NM, LP)     |
| price      | real  | Card price in USD                |
| quantity   | int   | Quantity in stock                |
| rarity     | text  | Card rarity (e.g. Rare, Common)  |

---

## Database Schema

```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS users (
    id            INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    first_name    TEXT    NOT NULL,
    last_name     TEXT    NOT NULL,
    email         TEXT    NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    password_hash TEXT    NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS cards (
    id        INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    name      TEXT,
    set_name  TEXT,
    condition TEXT,
    price     REAL,
    quantity  INTEGER,
    rarity    TEXT
);
```

---

## REST API Endpoints

### Auth & Users

| Name            | Method | Path           | Auth Required | Description                                  |
|-----------------|--------|----------------|---------------|----------------------------------------------|
| Register user   | POST   | `/users`        | No            | Create a new user account                    |
| Login           | POST   | `/auth/login`   | No            | Authenticate and receive a session ID        |
| Logout          | POST   | `/auth/logout`  | No            | Destroy the current session                  |

#### POST `/users` — Request body
```json
{
  "first_name": "Jane",
  "last_name": "Smith",
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}
```
Returns `201` with user object on success; `409` if email already exists.

#### POST `/auth/login` — Request body
```json
{ "email": "jane@example.com", "password": "secret123" }
```
Returns `200` with `{ session_id, user }` on success; `401` on failure.

### Cards (all require `X-Session-ID` header)

| Name         | Method | Path               | Description                  |
|--------------|--------|--------------------|------------------------------|
| List cards   | GET    | `/cards`            | Retrieve all cards            |
| Get card     | GET    | `/cards/<id>`       | Retrieve a single card        |
| Create card  | POST   | `/cards`            | Add a new card                |
| Update card  | PUT    | `/cards/<id>`       | Update an existing card       |
| Delete card  | DELETE | `/cards/<id>`       | Delete a card                 |

All card endpoints return `401 Unauthorized` if `X-Session-ID` is missing or invalid.

---

## Password Hashing

| Parameter  | Value                        |
|------------|------------------------------|
| Algorithm  | PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA256           |
| Iterations | 260,000                      |
| Salt       | 32 bytes (cryptographically random, `os.urandom`) |
| Storage    | `<hex-salt>$<hex-digest>` stored in `password_hash` column |
| Comparison | `secrets.compare_digest` (timing-safe) |

Python's built-in `hashlib.pbkdf2_hmac` is used — no third-party libraries required. The plain-text password is never stored or logged.

---

## Session Store

Sessions are held in an **in-memory Python dictionary** (`SESSION_STORE`) on the server keyed by a 64-character cryptographically random hex token (`secrets.token_hex(32)`).

The session ID is stored in **`localStorage`** on the client and sent with every protected request via the `X-Session-ID` HTTP header.

### User Preferences
The following preferences persist in `localStorage` regardless of login state:

| Preference  | Key          | Options              |
|-------------|--------------|----------------------|
| Color mode  | `colorMode`  | `light`, `dark`      |
| View type   | `viewType`   | `grid`, `table`      |

---

## Running the App

```bash
pip install flask
python server.py
```

Open any `.html` file in a browser (or serve with a static server). The API runs at `http://localhost:5000`.